  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">International Cooperation with Bahrain</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It consists of technical and advisory support in developing Bahrain&#x2019;s national adaptation investment plan, with an adaptation project pipeline in its core, addressing the most pressing climate change adaptation needs, and considering other planning elements including but not limited to a comprehensive climate finance and investment strategy, and implementation arrangements.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through the national adaptation investment plan (NAIP) process, Bahrain will increase its climate action readiness, through identifying short- and long-term priority options on climate change adaptation based on available data on current and future climate change impacts. The existing in-country risk assessment studies formed the basis of identifying and prioritizing the adaptation options targeting the most critical sectors. Bahrain&#x2019;s National Communication identifies the following key areas as the most vulnerable ones: (1) coastal zones, (2) water resources, (3) human health, and (4) biodiversity.</narrative>
  </description>
